<!--
    PUF France Use Case 3: Invoice Paid by Third-Party PAYER Known at Invoicing
    (Facture à payer par un tiers PAYEUR connu au moment de la facturation)
    
    Business Scenario:
    - Known third-party PAYER will pay the ENTIRE invoice to SELLER
    - Invoice transmitted to BUYER for validation/approval
    - BUYER manages third-party payment process
    - Payment not yet made (unlike UC2 - already paid)
    
    Key Requirements:
    - Business process B1: Standard invoice (payment arrangement doesn't change invoice type)
    - Third-party PAYER: EXT-FR-FE-BG-02 (mandatory for UC3)
    - BT-115 (Amount due) = BT-112 (full amount still owed)
    - No prepaid amount (payment will be made by third party after approval)
    
    Workflow:
    1. SELLER creates invoice, transmits to BUYER via PPF
    2. BUYER validates/approves invoice
    3. BUYER notifies third-party PAYER of approved invoice
    4. Third-party PAYER pays SELLER
    5. BUYER transmits "Paiement Transmis" status
    6. SELLER receives payment, transmits "Encaissée" status
    
    French Text Codes (BT-21/BT-22):
    - #REG#: Company legal form and share capital
    - #ABL#: Trade register number (RCS)
    - #AAI#: APE business activity code
    - #PMD#: Late payment penalties
    - #PMT#: Fixed collection costs indemnity (€40)
    - #BAR#: Treatment type (B2B e-invoicing)
    - #PAI#: Third party payment information
-->
<Invoice xmlns="urn:pagero:PageroUniversalFormat:Invoice:1.0" xmlns:cac="urn:pagero:CommonAggregateComponents:1.0" xmlns:cbc="urn:oasis:names:specification:ubl:schema:xsd:CommonBasicComponents-2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:puf="urn:pagero:ExtensionComponent:1.0" xmlns:ext="urn:oasis:names:specification:ubl:schema:xsd:CommonExtensionComponents-2">

